<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aean on 03-21-2001 12:25 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I'm afraid I have to agree with everyone about smithing. My skill is at 176 and i haven't made anything in over a month. The prices to make FS are way off the mark and Cultural armours there is no way in hell you can sell that stuff.

just for some reference here's some stats and prices, each piece is the breastplate or their respective armour types and the cost (aprox) to make and how much it typically sells for.

Banded BP  AC15 costs roughly 6-7 plat to make and sells for 15 plat
Ornate Chain AC16 cost IF you buy the ingredients from vendors it's roughly 100 plat, i've never made it so i can't say how much it sells for but lets just say it wouldn't sell :P
Bronze BP AC17 drops off of mobs so it's free to make and sells for 34plat
Fine Steel Breastplate AC19 costs aprox 110plat to make and I usually sell them for 300plat
Field Breastplate AC20, a non imbued version costs me roughly 400plat not including time to gather ingredients so if I wanna make money i have to triple the price to make up for failures so roughly 1200plat for 1 BP, needless to say I have never filled an order for one of those.
Now for some real fun, Imbued Fieldbreastplate of Mith Marr, add that 400 to 1k for a diamond and thats 1400 a shot, which I have failed on by the way. triple that and it's 4200:/ there's no way in hell anyone is gonna buy that off me.

So to make a long story short smithing is only good if you either have lots of money to blow and just wanna try it or you are the guild smith, or if there is a specific piece of armour you want and you wanna make it for yourself.

[This message has been edited by Aean (edited 03-21-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
